Description: Small fragment of a seal-impression, the fine brown Nile clay has some mica inclusions and was hardened after excavation. The rear shows a flat area, slightly concave with the impression of wood, possibly from a box or similar, a second side shows remains of a string impressions. The front shows quite some finger impressions and a part of an oval scarab-like seal. The remaining part shows a seated figure, facing to the right with a sun disc above the head. No further signs visible.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), E14.7 temple magazine
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
